result.adr_address: 37號 Mut Wah St, Kwun Tong, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 37號 Mut Wah St, Kwun Tong, Hong Kong
result.name: Eat To New

reviews.text:
2nd time in Hong Kong, 2nd visit. Not sure why there is no review of this place - it's pretty good. Maybe there is a Hong Kong local Google site not displayed in English.

- 95% of the diners looks like locals living around the area (good indication of how good it is)
- tables are pretty spaced out apart, unlike restaurant where you sit nearly elbow to elbow
- tables can cater for groups of up to 6 (tight squeeze but possible)
- the oyster porridge is pretty darn good. Fresh oysters in Hong Kong style rice congee. Nearly home cook style + a cup of hot tea (came up to HKD51)
- there is a more popular restaurant just a couple of doors down (Ocean View) but I reckon this one winds hands down
- opens quite late. Had supper at 9.30pm and they still don't look like they were closing
- very wide menu range. Can't speak Cantonese? Just point and order on the menu
